The paper uses Natural Language Processing techniques to retrieve historical information from Wikipedia, which suggests a focus on information retrieval and text analysis (cs.CL). The analysis of mobility patterns and geographical networks suggests a focus on social networks and computational social science (cs.SOC). The use of a multilevel radiation model for human mobility suggests a focus on spatial analysis and modeling (cs.CY). The paper also deals with historical data and cultural development, which could fall under the categories of digital humanities (cs.DL) and social impact (cs.SI).
